1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,156
Uncle, you have the blueprints
of the hospital, right?

2
00:00:06,202 --> 00:00:07,726
Must be on my table.

3
00:00:08,370 --> 00:00:09,394
Search it.

4
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:12,598
Oh, boy.

5
00:00:13,909 --> 00:00:14,876
What happened?

6
00:00:15,711 --> 00:00:19,340
How can you keep such
confidential papers like this?

7
00:00:22,218 --> 00:00:25,745
How many times have I told you...
I need an assistant...

8
00:00:40,903 --> 00:00:44,100
Heritage Hotel project. Our home?

9
00:00:47,910 --> 00:00:49,775
Our home... a hotel?

10
00:00:58,921 --> 00:01:01,719
See what Lolita's got me
with her first pay?

11
00:01:02,258 --> 00:01:03,725
Chocolate. For me?

12
00:01:03,926 --> 00:01:06,121
Can't you ever buy
something for yourself?

13
00:01:09,431 --> 00:01:12,992
Silly girl.
- What if uncle finds out?

14
00:01:14,436 --> 00:01:15,733
What are you looking at?

15
00:01:27,021 --> 00:01:29,581
How much time do we
have to vacate?

16
00:01:29,858 --> 00:01:34,989
End of November, I think.

17
00:01:35,196 --> 00:01:38,256
This can't happen.

18
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:41,600
Navin uncle can't do this.

19
00:01:43,204 --> 00:01:47,004
A profitless deal is a bad one.

20
00:01:47,542 --> 00:01:50,170
I have to repay by 30th November.

21
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:52,847
Can I ever repay?

22
00:02:03,925 --> 00:02:06,120
Tell me what do you want?

23
00:02:06,561 --> 00:02:09,928
I could ask Shekhar...

24
00:02:10,098 --> 00:02:14,194
but will he have 150,000...?

25
00:02:14,402 --> 00:02:15,960
Here, keep the key.

26
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,456
Didn't you hear the horn?

27
00:02:43,932 --> 00:02:48,062
I'll drop you if you're
on your way home.

28
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:56,240
A profit less deal is a bad one.

29
00:02:58,112 --> 00:03:03,744
Navin Rai though a gentleman
is also a businessman.

30
00:03:11,125 --> 00:03:13,593
Oh, hello. - Hello.

31
00:03:13,795 --> 00:03:16,764
Did you meet him on
the way, Lolita?

32
00:03:18,132 --> 00:03:21,260
Where have you been all
these days, Gurucharan?

33
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:24,939
I wanted to show you
my face only after...

34
00:03:25,306 --> 00:03:30,266
...l'd organized at least
part of your money.

35
00:03:32,146 --> 00:03:34,273
Money isn't going to disappear
all of a sudden, are they?

36
00:03:34,649 --> 00:03:36,446
Return at your leisure.

37
00:03:36,985 --> 00:03:39,510
Ridiculous. I'm your neighbour,
not a businessman.

38
00:03:41,489 --> 00:03:44,049
You've retired now, relax.

39
00:03:45,994 --> 00:03:49,953
Stop worrying.
We'll find some way.

40
00:03:50,665 --> 00:03:51,859
Let's go, uncle.

41
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,626
Goodbye.

42
00:03:53,835 --> 00:03:54,529
Let's go.

43
00:03:59,340 --> 00:04:01,205
He's taken a load off me.

44
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:04,478
Let's all celebrate with your
aunt's spinach cutlets.

45
00:04:04,679 --> 00:04:10,311
I know you love them.
I'm going to eat so much.

46
00:04:11,352 --> 00:04:12,410
Raghu.

47
00:04:22,363 --> 00:04:23,227
Anything else?

48
00:04:23,698 --> 00:04:31,104
Just one, sir, where will Lolita and
her family go after eviction?

49
00:04:31,372 --> 00:04:39,336
I mean, everything is ready
from our end... we're ready.

50
00:04:41,049 --> 00:04:42,846
We're getting a house worth...

51
00:04:43,051 --> 00:04:44,518
...two million for just 150,000...

52
00:04:45,219 --> 00:04:49,849
...surely we can give them
10 or 20,000 as good will.

53
00:04:50,058 --> 00:04:50,786
Yes, sir.

54
00:04:51,225 --> 00:04:54,786
We won't throw them out.
They can stay in our old warehouse.

55
00:04:55,063 --> 00:04:57,861
But that place...?

56
00:04:58,066 --> 00:05:03,197
Get it cleaned, get some electricity...
they can stay...

57
00:05:03,404 --> 00:05:04,701
...there for a few days.

58
00:05:05,573 --> 00:05:09,031
In any case, their house is
too classy for them.

59
00:05:10,244 --> 00:05:15,546
True. But won't Shekhar's presence...?

60
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,377
Don't worry.

61
00:05:17,919 --> 00:05:23,551
Shekhar will be in Darjeeling
finalizing the Tea Estate deal.

62
00:05:23,758 --> 00:05:27,285
At least you can sleep peacefully now.

63
00:05:27,595 --> 00:05:30,564
Otherwise we kept getting visitors.

64
00:05:30,765 --> 00:05:35,065
But the debt still exists, and
we still have to pay it back.

65
00:05:35,436 --> 00:05:42,842
Now you've started.
Hasn't Navin Rai just said...

66
00:05:43,444 --> 00:05:46,641
Words don't mean anything.
We must repay him.

67
00:05:47,115 --> 00:05:49,982
Who has that kind of money?

68
00:05:50,785 --> 00:05:57,418
I have some money... and
we can sell mother's jewelery.

69
00:05:58,459 --> 00:06:06,093
What? Sell sister's jewelery?
What's the matter with you?

70
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:15,332
How do I explain to you
that unless we repay him...

71
00:06:15,476 --> 00:06:19,606
Don't worry daughter.
Please don't cry.

72
00:06:20,314 --> 00:06:22,282
Have some faith in Navin Rai.

73
00:06:22,483 --> 00:06:24,007
Hello, uncle. Hello, aunty.

74
00:06:24,318 --> 00:06:25,285
Hello, Sunita.

75
00:06:25,486 --> 00:06:27,784
Have a sweet. Charu's engaged.

76
00:06:27,989 --> 00:06:28,887
Is it?

77
00:06:29,323 --> 00:06:31,689
Why the long face?

78
00:06:31,993 --> 00:06:33,517
You've to make
the arrangements, right?

79
00:06:33,828 --> 00:06:35,352
Come on, we have to
select saris for the wedding.

80
00:06:35,563 --> 00:06:36,791
When is it?

81
00:06:36,998 --> 00:06:38,966
After the festival... on the 19th.

82
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:40,634
So soon?

83
00:06:40,835 --> 00:06:43,303
I know. But the priest says
it's a very auspicious day.

84
00:06:43,504 --> 00:06:44,630
Just need to exchange garlands...

85
00:06:44,839 --> 00:06:46,807
You can't call that a wedding?

86
00:06:47,008 --> 00:06:50,967
Exactly. It's such an auspicious day
that, that's all you need.

87
00:06:51,179 --> 00:06:54,637
No, our Charu will go
amid a lot of fanfare.

88
00:06:54,849 --> 00:06:55,645
Absolutely.

89
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:57,249
Let's go.

90
00:06:57,518 --> 00:06:58,985
No, I have to go to Shekhar's.

91
00:06:59,187 --> 00:07:04,648
I've just come from there...
he's out. Go later.

92
00:07:04,859 --> 00:07:07,657
Go, it'll brighten your mood.

93
00:07:07,862 --> 00:07:09,489
Guess what... yesterday Girish
was to come...

94
00:07:09,697 --> 00:07:10,322
...shopping with me

95
00:07:10,531 --> 00:07:11,498
...He didn't come with me...

96
00:07:11,699 --> 00:07:12,996
and he never listens to me.

97
00:07:13,701 --> 00:07:15,498
One second... - Yes.

98
00:07:15,703 --> 00:07:18,263
Is Shekhar back? - Not yet.

99
00:07:18,539 --> 00:07:21,007
Please let me know once he does.

100
00:07:21,209 --> 00:07:22,005
OK.

101
00:07:23,044 --> 00:07:26,013
Enter only if you're in peace.

102
00:07:26,214 --> 00:07:28,774
Has the fuse blown again?

103
00:07:28,983 --> 00:07:30,007
Let me show you the sari
I've picked out...

104
00:07:30,218 --> 00:07:32,413
Here comes the ghost. I'm off.

105
00:07:35,056 --> 00:07:36,683
There's a wedding to organize

106
00:07:36,891 --> 00:07:38,358
and you're sitting
with the planchette.

107
00:07:38,759 --> 00:07:39,589
Please sit, sis.

108
00:07:40,228 --> 00:07:41,695
Ask something, sis.

109
00:07:41,896 --> 00:07:43,693
The spirit's here already?

110
00:07:43,898 --> 00:07:47,629
Ask something, sis? Come on...

111
00:07:54,575 --> 00:07:55,439
I've asked.

112
00:07:55,910 --> 00:08:00,040
And here's your answer...

113
00:08:00,248 --> 00:08:15,721
P-R-O-B-L-E-M-S-O-L-V-E-D

114
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:21,562
Sis, consider your problem solved.
What's the problem?

115
00:08:21,769 --> 00:08:22,895
Sis...?

116
00:08:24,605 --> 00:08:26,800
What's up? - Nothing.

117
00:08:30,278 --> 00:08:35,238
Now lets see who will solve it?

118
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:43,415
Girish.

119
00:08:43,624 --> 00:08:44,249
Girish? - Girish?

120
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:50,419
Brother, you'll solve her...
yes, with a magnet.

121
00:08:50,631 --> 00:08:52,758
What's this, Girish?
- Cheating. No...

122
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:54,832
I hate such pranks.

123
00:08:55,469 --> 00:08:58,597
Lolita, Shekhar's back.

124
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,937
I have to go.

125
00:09:05,313 --> 00:09:07,110
Who's this Shekhar?

126
00:09:07,315 --> 00:09:08,782
How come you're here tonight?

127
00:09:09,317 --> 00:09:10,443
Shekhar, please.

128
00:09:11,652 --> 00:09:12,380
What happened?

129
00:09:14,155 --> 00:09:15,622
I need some money.

130
00:09:16,324 --> 00:09:18,792
Why ask? You have the key.

131
00:09:21,996 --> 00:09:23,964
I need a bit more.

132
00:09:24,665 --> 00:09:25,632
How much?

133
00:09:28,002 --> 00:09:28,969
150,000 rupees.

134
00:09:29,503 --> 00:09:34,805
What? Are you buying a plane?
Direct to London, huh?

135
00:09:35,343 --> 00:09:41,976
Please stop joking.
I really need that much.

136
00:09:48,689 --> 00:09:53,888
Why? What happened?

137
00:09:54,095 --> 00:09:54,754
Shekhar... I...

138
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:01,558
Shekhar. - Yes, father.

139
00:10:04,038 --> 00:10:07,838
Sidharth's coming here to
discuss your Darjeeling trip.

140
00:10:08,042 --> 00:10:09,168
Come to the study.

141
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,108
Now.

142
00:10:26,394 --> 00:10:31,422
They will lose their ancestral home
worth two million for

143
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:32,997
just 150,000?

144
00:10:33,901 --> 00:10:36,529
If I could I'd give it to them
and ask them to fling

145
00:10:36,737 --> 00:10:38,364
it on Navin Rai's face.

146
00:10:38,572 --> 00:10:40,199
I have that much. - What?

147
00:10:40,741 --> 00:10:44,040
I can give them the money.
- But why?

148
00:10:44,245 --> 00:10:51,481
Sis, its just 11,252 pounds.

149
00:10:51,752 --> 00:10:56,382
While we celebrate
Charu's wedding.

150
00:10:56,590 --> 00:11:00,048
Imagine them on the streets

151
00:11:00,428 --> 00:11:03,397
True. If you can,

152
00:11:03,597 --> 00:11:05,895
please do something.
God will bless you.

153
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,158
I will.

154
00:11:07,435 --> 00:11:16,901
But is that the only reason,
or... Lolita. Aha. Lolita.

155
00:11:17,111 --> 00:11:20,239
Sis, can't you take anything
at face value?

156
00:11:20,448 --> 00:11:25,750
Have you seen yours
it's bright red.

157
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,247
You're too much, sis.

158
00:11:34,295 --> 00:11:38,595
I can't believe this, son.

159
00:11:40,801 --> 00:11:41,927
Girish is making me...

160
00:11:42,136 --> 00:11:45,333
...his Managing Partner
in his new project.

161
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:47,197
Managing Partner? - Yes.

162
00:11:47,475 --> 00:11:52,936
And, he's given me five years'
pay in advance too.

163
00:11:53,147 --> 00:11:55,775
180,000 rupees...

164
00:11:58,486 --> 00:12:00,113
with no interest.

165
00:12:00,488 --> 00:12:07,621
Uncle, it's your salary,
not a debt.

166
00:12:07,828 --> 00:12:11,286
But son, at this age...? - What?

167
00:12:11,499 --> 00:12:13,626
I'm a textile man...

168
00:12:13,834 --> 00:12:17,964
You're a man of principles, uncle.

169
00:12:20,007 --> 00:12:23,033
I need your values and experience.

170
00:12:24,512 --> 00:12:25,979
Hear that?

171
00:12:27,681 --> 00:12:30,377
OK, son. I'll accept this.

172
00:12:31,352 --> 00:12:33,650
Our problems have disappeared.

173
00:12:34,188 --> 00:12:36,486
Though Navin Rai is a gentleman...

174
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:42,253
Even so... a debt should be
repaid as fast as possible.

175
00:12:42,363 --> 00:12:47,995
You're right, son.
I'll keep this inside.

176
00:13:13,561 --> 00:13:20,524
Oh, no. No tears now.
Let's celebrate. Get dressed now.

177
00:13:20,734 --> 00:13:21,530
Why?

178
00:13:21,902 --> 00:13:23,961
Girish, haven't you told her?

179
00:13:24,405 --> 00:13:28,364
Yeah, it's a double celebration
at Trinca's...

180
00:13:28,542 --> 00:13:33,570
For Charu's wedding and...
do you have a headache today?

181
00:13:35,082 --> 00:13:41,317
Come on get dressed now.
And sis, wear my heels if you like.

182
00:13:41,755 --> 00:13:43,552
I'm fine in these flats.
I'm not going to fall.

183
00:13:44,592 --> 00:13:45,718
Hurry up.

184
00:13:47,928 --> 00:13:50,055
How will we all fit?

185
00:13:50,264 --> 00:13:52,061
In a big heart.

186
00:13:53,601 --> 00:13:55,000
Come on.

187
00:13:56,937 --> 00:13:59,735
And Keol, try not to
mess up my shirt today.

188
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:03,899
What is this riddle called life?

189
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:12,041
Can you block it, can you
stop that which flows?

190
00:14:47,321 --> 00:14:48,379
Good Morning.

191
00:14:48,822 --> 00:14:53,282
Good morning. How's everything?

192
00:14:53,494 --> 00:14:54,961
Your money.

193
00:14:56,997 --> 00:14:58,624
Money?

194
00:14:58,832 --> 00:15:01,733
The mortgage... exactly 150,000 rupees.

195
00:15:03,671 --> 00:15:05,639
How did you get so much money?

196
00:15:05,839 --> 00:15:07,864
Met a gentlemen just like you.

197
00:15:08,075 --> 00:15:09,633
Impossible.

198
00:15:10,177 --> 00:15:12,145
Did you get burnt?

199
00:15:14,348 --> 00:15:17,806
You can't mortgage an
already mortgaged house.

200
00:15:18,018 --> 00:15:23,820
It's not like that.
Girish... oh, you don't know him.

201
00:15:24,024 --> 00:15:27,824
He's made me his Managing Partner.

202
00:15:28,195 --> 00:15:32,154
Thought the least I can do
is repay your money as

203
00:15:32,366 --> 00:15:33,663
I can never repay your kindness.

204
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,767
Please take it.

205
00:15:43,544 --> 00:15:47,571
Just need your signature here.

206
00:16:00,394 --> 00:16:03,124
Now if I could just have
my house papers please...

207
00:16:15,743 --> 00:16:18,712
Hello, uncle. - Hello, son.
Meeting with dad?

208
00:16:18,912 --> 00:16:21,938
Yes. The Goddess has
been very kind.

209
00:16:22,049 --> 00:16:25,177
I've repaid my entire debt,
with interest.

210
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:27,387
Really?

211
00:16:27,921 --> 00:16:30,549
The Goddess sent him from
London just to help us.

212
00:16:31,258 --> 00:16:37,959
Imagine, 180,000 rupees.
See you, son.

213
00:16:38,432 --> 00:16:40,491
Do come in the evening
for the prayers.

214
00:18:04,184 --> 00:18:05,481
Hey, what are you doing?

215
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,817
Might burn your feet.

216
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:40,509
Come on, aunt... the clothes are
yours, so are the earrings...

217
00:18:40,721 --> 00:18:42,416
...and now this necklace - why?

218
00:18:43,557 --> 00:18:47,857
You're mine too, aren't you?

219
00:18:48,896 --> 00:18:57,531
Stay away from the evil eye today...
you look beautiful.

220
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:10,316
I hope you marry a prince,
and rule where ever you go.

221
00:19:10,517 --> 00:19:15,045
Let's go.
Sunita has called five times.

222
00:19:15,255 --> 00:19:17,723
Now go.
Get my prince ready.

223
00:19:18,091 --> 00:19:19,319
Why?

224
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:23,992
He's sulking.
Just like his father.

225
00:19:24,264 --> 00:19:26,391
Says he's lost his buttons and chain.

226
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,898
You mean his sense of humour.

227
00:19:29,269 --> 00:19:33,330
Get him ready quickly.
Just fifteen minutes left. - OK.

228
00:19:38,445 --> 00:19:42,142
Just fifteen minutes left
and you're not ready yet?

229
00:19:43,116 --> 00:19:46,176
Now smoke your health away.

230
00:19:46,386 --> 00:19:48,820
I know what's good for me.

231
00:19:49,022 --> 00:19:58,590
Why the temper? Brilliant excuse not to
show up though can't find my
buttons and chain.' So what's this?

232
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:01,122
I don't want to go.

233
00:20:01,969 --> 00:20:03,231
Why?

234
00:20:03,437 --> 00:20:04,495
Is this a marriage?

235
00:20:04,972 --> 00:20:08,772
No conversation, no engagement
just a cold wedding invitation.

236
00:20:08,976 --> 00:20:09,704
I'm not in the mood.

237
00:20:11,111 --> 00:20:13,705
Weddings are dictated by an
auspicious moment... not your mood.

238
00:20:13,914 --> 00:20:17,645
And they say tonight
is particularly auspicious.

239
00:20:17,851 --> 00:20:20,411
Exchange garlands, and you're married.

240
00:20:21,154 --> 00:20:23,315
I said I'm not going.

241
00:20:23,523 --> 00:20:24,581
What's up with you?

242
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:27,225
No - what's up with all of you?

243
00:20:27,427 --> 00:20:28,792
What do you mean?

244
00:20:28,996 --> 00:20:31,726
You, uncle...

245
00:20:32,733 --> 00:20:37,170
Why did you take money
from that stranger?

246
00:20:37,371 --> 00:20:38,929
Did father ever ask for the money?

247
00:20:40,741 --> 00:20:42,470
Do you know why Girish helped you?

248
00:20:43,343 --> 00:20:44,207
Tell me.

249
00:20:45,045 --> 00:20:46,637
To buy you.

250
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,743
Moulin Rouge, bailing you
out with money...

251
00:20:48,949 --> 00:20:50,177
I could've helped you.

252
00:20:50,384 --> 00:20:51,180
And I did ask you.

253
00:20:51,385 --> 00:20:55,219
But you didn't wait.
Why did you go to him?

254
00:20:55,422 --> 00:20:56,821
Where would you have
got that money from?

255
00:20:57,024 --> 00:21:00,152
Why don't you understand?
I could've asked father.

256
00:21:01,628 --> 00:21:04,620
And have us repay your father
with his own money?

257
00:21:05,399 --> 00:21:13,602
Do you even know what he...
anyway. Thank God, it's over.

